DSA-001B

### **Definition:**

To find the largest number among A, B, and C using nested decision-making.

**Logic Flow (Pseudocode)**

```
Start

â†“

Input A, B, C

â†“

If A > B

â†’ If A > C â†’ Print A

â†’ Else â†’ Print C

Else

â†’ If B > C â†’ Print B

â†’ Else â†’ Print C

â†“

End
```

### ðŸ§  Concept Summary (in 1 line):

> Compare A > B, then check A > C or B > C, whichever is bigger â†’ print it.
> 

**ðŸ’» Code**

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class MaxOfThree {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int c = sc.nextInt();

        if (a > b) {
            if (a > c)
                System.out.println("Max: " + a);
            else
                System.out.println("Max: " + c);
        } else {
            if (b > c)
                System.out.println("Max: " + b);
            else
                System.out.println("Max: " + c);
        }
    }
}

```
